@wycdd @Obstropolos @SpruceID @openid Well, yes. But we were early ‚Äî and our product experience sucked and didn't have the same incentives/context that y'all have today. Fortunately many of us have spread throughout industry and are on the inside. @bluesky is sympatico, as I understand it. Right @willnorris?

@wycdd @Obstropolos @SpruceID @openid I hear you. I'm honestly not sure how useful the Big Tech Co implementations would be. I imagine they've enormous snake pits of complexity. But as a co-author of OAuth, I felt the record needed to be corrected. Hell, we went out of our way to create a patent non-assert regime!

@wycdd @Obstropolos I didn't say anything about those implementations; I was referring to the authoring of the open standards that define the protocols. Protocol openness & interop is more important than source, but still, here's some code: https://t.co/wrmgduhQ6X
